266
00:17:18,940 --> 00:17:20,039
I don't want you...

267
00:17:21,210 --> 00:17:23,279
to take this the wrong way.

268
00:17:23,950 --> 00:17:26,279
I'm just saying this...

269
00:17:26,950 --> 00:17:30,150
out of worry as his doctor.

270
00:17:30,150 --> 00:17:33,859
If that's not enough,
think of this situation...

271
00:17:34,430 --> 00:17:36,890
as a father who's worried
about his son.

272
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:39,630
Okay.

273
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:42,470
I'm fine. Please, speak comfortably.

274
00:17:43,069 --> 00:17:48,069
That woman was special to him.

275
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:50,509
She was his first love.

276
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:54,609
After Seo Yeon passed away,
he was in so much pain.

277
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:58,319
"Seo Yeon"?

278
00:17:59,019 --> 00:18:01,049
Yes. Her name was Jung Seo Yeon.

279
00:18:04,190 --> 00:18:08,059
I'm happy that he was able
to meet someone new...

280
00:18:08,559 --> 00:18:11,730
after losing her.

281
00:18:12,900 --> 00:18:15,099
But I can't help
but feel worried as well.

282
00:18:17,099 --> 00:18:21,369
He will always have her
in his heart.

283
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:27,180
Will you be okay with that?

284
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:32,549
I'm okay with everything...

285
00:18:35,119 --> 00:18:37,049
as long as he's happy.

286
00:18:38,490 --> 00:18:39,859
I'm okay.

287
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:42,990
Thank you for your concern.

288
00:18:49,329 --> 00:18:51,539
I told you I didn't remember
my first love.

289
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,440
That was a lie.

290
00:18:53,799 --> 00:18:55,640
I still haven't gotten over her.

291
00:18:56,970 --> 00:18:58,410
I still love her.

292
00:19:04,650 --> 00:19:05,849
Do you know...

293
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:08,390
someone named Jung Seo Yeon?

294
00:19:12,420 --> 00:19:15,329
I had a friend
who got into a similar accident.

295
00:19:16,529 --> 00:19:19,359
That's why I was concerned
and sensitive about you.

296
00:19:29,670 --> 00:19:31,710
I'm okay with everything...

297
00:19:32,279 --> 00:19:34,680
as long as he's happy.

298
00:19:52,059 --> 00:19:53,299
Hey, Professor Kim.

299
00:19:54,670 --> 00:19:56,529
I have a favor to ask you.

300
00:19:57,869 --> 00:20:00,400
I want to meet with Moon Seong Ho.

301
00:20:02,369 --> 00:20:03,369
What?

302
00:20:05,309 --> 00:20:06,509
Which hospital?

303
00:20:16,049 --> 00:20:18,920
I'm going to change
your gauze and bandage.

304
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:29,829
(Ward A to C, Reception,
Treatment Room, Waiting Area)

305
00:20:30,369 --> 00:20:32,269
- I'm here to see...
- You're here.

306
00:20:32,269 --> 00:20:35,140
Hey. So Moon Seong Ho
tried to kill himself?

307
00:20:35,140 --> 00:20:37,470
What on earth is this about?
How is he now?

308
00:20:37,470 --> 00:20:39,440
Luckily, the doctor reattached
the blood vessel.

309
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:41,450
So it's not life-threatening.

310
00:20:42,180 --> 00:20:45,180
But he's psychologically unstable.

311
00:20:45,650 --> 00:20:49,450
I don't think he can have
any visitors for the time being.

312
00:20:49,450 --> 00:20:51,220
But can you help me out here?

313
00:20:51,789 --> 00:20:54,630
As you know, he tries
to kill himself all the time.

314
00:20:54,630 --> 00:20:58,029
But this is the first time he
actually injured himself this badly.

315
00:20:58,029 --> 00:20:59,799
It could be really dangerous
for you.

316
00:20:59,799 --> 00:21:01,970
I can control him.

317
00:21:01,970 --> 00:21:03,569
I'll make sure
you don't get burned for this.

318
00:21:03,569 --> 00:21:06,039
Just allow me to see him
for 30 minutes.

319
00:21:06,339 --> 00:21:07,640
My gosh.

320
00:21:15,809 --> 00:21:16,950
Nice to meet you.

321
00:21:17,809 --> 00:21:19,950
My name is Yoo Sung Hyuk.

322
00:21:22,849 --> 00:21:25,390
I invited myself in here
because I thought...

323
00:21:25,390 --> 00:21:27,690
it'd be nice for us to talk.
I hope you don't mind.

324
00:21:30,990 --> 00:21:33,359
What's outside the window?

325
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:35,569
It looks like
you're staring at the sky.

326
00:21:37,569 --> 00:21:39,400
Did Seo Yeon say something to you?

327
00:21:44,809 --> 00:21:46,039
Do you know her?

328
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,049
Of course.

329
00:21:52,279 --> 00:21:54,380
I used to be
Anchor Lee Jeong Hoon's...

330
00:21:55,390 --> 00:21:57,890
doctor for a long time.

331
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:00,660
You're that jerk's doctor?

332
00:22:02,029 --> 00:22:04,160
I wanted to talk to you...

333
00:22:05,130 --> 00:22:08,170
because I wanted to find out
something about Anchor Lee.

334
00:22:09,930 --> 00:22:11,170
What do you say?

335
00:22:11,839 --> 00:22:14,000
Are you interested
in talking to me now?

336
00:22:31,990 --> 00:22:34,519
I'm sure you know the woman...

337
00:22:35,059 --> 00:22:37,289
Anchor Lee is dating now.

338
00:22:38,059 --> 00:22:40,130
She's an actress named Yeo Ha Jin.

339
00:22:42,130 --> 00:22:44,200
I heard she used to
be Seo Yeon's friend.

340
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:50,509
So I can sort of understand...

341
00:22:51,339 --> 00:22:55,950
how Lee Jeong Hoon, Jung Seo Yeon,
and Yeo Ha Jin are connected.

342
00:22:56,410 --> 00:22:58,549
But I'm curious...

343
00:22:59,220 --> 00:23:02,220
about how you fit into all of this.
That intrigues me.

344
00:23:04,119 --> 00:23:06,690
- Aren't you Jeong Hoon's doctor?
- Yes.

345
00:23:06,690 --> 00:23:08,730
Why are you asking me that?

346
00:23:10,089 --> 00:23:12,460
Your patient is Lee Jeong Hoon,
not me.

347
00:23:12,859 --> 00:23:14,829
I want to know the truth.

348
00:23:15,329 --> 00:23:18,240
Sometimes,
patients lie to their doctors...

349
00:23:18,799 --> 00:23:21,640
because they want other people
to say that they are normal,

350
00:23:23,240 --> 00:23:26,640
but you see,
I'm not that easy to fool.

351
00:23:37,650 --> 00:23:38,819
So...

352
00:23:40,059 --> 00:23:41,730
you want me...

353
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:45,559
to tell you the truth?

354
00:23:50,529 --> 00:23:52,400
Can you help me up?

355
00:24:01,549 --> 00:24:03,109
Where are the scissors?

356
00:24:03,779 --> 00:24:05,920
I definitely had a pair
when I went in...

357
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:07,619
to check on the prisoner
serving a life sentence.

358
00:24:08,049 --> 00:24:09,650
Moon Seong Ho, what are you doing?

359
00:24:09,650 --> 00:24:10,990
Put that down now!

360
00:24:10,990 --> 00:24:13,420
You should be careful
with your guns.

361
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,730
Do you want to see him die?

362
00:24:15,829 --> 00:24:16,890
I doubt that.

363
00:24:17,029 --> 00:24:18,089
Put the gun down and step back.

364
00:24:18,089 --> 00:24:19,630
Hey, Moon Seong Ho.

365
00:24:20,059 --> 00:24:22,500
- Don't get worked up. You and I...
- Easy, easy.

366
00:24:22,970 --> 00:24:25,039
Keep your mouth shut
unless you want to die.

367
00:24:25,039 --> 00:24:28,210
Don't tell me this was
all part of your plan.

368
00:24:28,210 --> 00:24:29,940
Well, not really.

369
00:24:30,470 --> 00:24:32,509
But thanks to you,
things have gotten very easier.

370
00:24:32,509 --> 00:24:33,609
Hey, guys.

371
00:24:33,839 --> 00:24:35,549
I'm not scared of dying.

372
00:24:35,609 --> 00:24:36,910
But you are.

373
00:24:37,809 --> 00:24:39,950
If this guy dies,
you'll be in big trouble.

374
00:24:39,950 --> 00:24:42,019
Don't do this. Just tell them...

375
00:24:42,019 --> 00:24:43,650
- your demand.
- I told you to be quiet.

376
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:44,720
What do you want?

377
00:24:44,890 --> 00:24:46,519
Let go of the hostage first.

378
00:24:48,190 --> 00:24:49,289
This hurts.

379
00:24:51,130 --> 00:24:52,859
- Hey.
- Don't come near me.

380
00:24:52,859 --> 00:24:54,559
- Stay there.
- Put down the scissors.

381
00:24:54,559 --> 00:24:55,900
- Don't come near me.
- Put that down!

382
00:24:56,569 --> 00:24:58,299
I told you to stay there.

383
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:01,569
- Sir!
- Get him.

384
00:25:07,380 --> 00:25:08,380
Come back here!

385
00:25:10,910 --> 00:25:12,119
- Darn it.
- The staircase on the other side.

386
00:25:15,220 --> 00:25:16,220
Are you all right?

387
00:25:22,730 --> 00:25:24,460
- Officer Jo, check the back.
- Yes, sir.

388
00:25:39,009 --> 00:25:41,240
It's all done. Rest up for now.
I'll call you once it's ready.

389
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,980
- Okay. Thank you.
- Sure.

390
00:25:55,990 --> 00:25:58,329
But I can't help
but feel worried as well.

391
00:25:59,059 --> 00:26:03,529
He will always have her
in his heart.

392
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:05,940
Will you be okay with that?

393
00:26:24,490 --> 00:26:27,690
Ha Jin, is it before your event?

394
00:26:28,190 --> 00:26:30,460
It was time, so I figured
your event already started.

395
00:26:30,460 --> 00:26:32,829
I'll start in about five minutes.

396
00:26:33,099 --> 00:26:35,400
I wanted to hear your voice
even for a few seconds.

397
00:26:37,170 --> 00:26:39,039
Then, do you want
to meet up afterward?

398
00:26:39,039 --> 00:26:40,569
I miss you too.

399
00:26:41,970 --> 00:26:43,240
Sure. Sounds great.

400
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:45,640
Okay. I'll go to your house later.

401
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:47,539
Why don't you rest up
after your event?

402
00:26:49,750 --> 00:26:52,450
By the way, I have a question.

403
00:26:54,519 --> 00:26:56,119
Are you happy now?

404
00:26:59,460 --> 00:27:01,089
You know my answer.

405
00:27:01,460 --> 00:27:03,430
But I still want to hear it
from you.

406
00:27:05,430 --> 00:27:07,960
I am in utter happiness.

407
00:27:11,329 --> 00:27:12,500
I'm glad to hear that.

408
00:27:14,039 --> 00:27:15,210
What about you, Ha Jin?

409
00:27:16,269 --> 00:27:17,839
I told you my answer.

410
00:27:18,809 --> 00:27:22,180
I said every single moment
I spend with you is precious to me.

411
00:27:22,279 --> 00:27:24,250
I am happy every single day now.

412
00:27:25,750 --> 00:27:26,880
I'm glad to hear that.

413
00:27:30,049 --> 00:27:32,160
I need to go in now.

414
00:27:32,890 --> 00:27:35,430
Okay. Good luck
with the signing event.

415
00:27:35,430 --> 00:27:36,660
See you later.

416
00:27:36,660 --> 00:27:37,660
Okay.

417
00:27:43,430 --> 00:27:45,670
Ha Jin, it's time. Let's go in.

418
00:27:45,970 --> 00:27:47,539
Okay. I'm coming.

419
00:27:48,170 --> 00:27:50,069
- Ha Jin!
- Ha Jin!

420
00:27:50,069 --> 00:27:51,210
- Ha Jin!
- Ha Jin!

421
00:27:51,210 --> 00:27:53,039
- Ha Jin.
- Ha Jin! You're so pretty!

422
00:27:53,039 --> 00:27:55,480
- I'm a huge fan.
- You're so pretty!

423
00:27:55,480 --> 00:27:57,049
- You're the best!
- Ha Jin!

424
00:27:57,150 --> 00:27:58,920
(Yeo Ha Jin's Fan Signing Event)

425
00:28:00,250 --> 00:28:02,519
- Ha Jin!
- Ha Jin, over here!

426
00:28:02,519 --> 00:28:05,519
- Ha Jin!
- You're so pretty!

427
00:28:07,660 --> 00:28:09,829
- Ha Jin, I love you!
- Ha Jin!

428
00:28:10,289 --> 00:28:11,529
- Ha Jin.
- Ha Jin! Over here!

429
00:28:13,599 --> 00:28:16,000
I've been dying to hold
a fan signing event.

430
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:18,670
When I got the offer,
I practically ran here.

431
00:28:18,670 --> 00:28:21,539
Since you're here,
please check out the store here.

432
00:28:21,839 --> 00:28:24,440
That way, I'll get to renew
my contract and hold another event.

433
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:25,940
- Okay!
- Yes!

434
00:28:25,940 --> 00:28:28,240
- I love you!
- You're so pretty!

435
00:28:28,240 --> 00:28:29,680
- Ha Jin!
- Ha Jin!

436
00:28:37,690 --> 00:28:40,460
What is it? What's with this uproar?

437
00:28:40,460 --> 00:28:41,990
There's a news flash.

438
00:28:41,990 --> 00:28:43,390
A news flash? What is it?

439
00:28:43,390 --> 00:28:45,430
Someone just ran away
from the National Forensic Hospital,

440
00:28:45,430 --> 00:28:47,230
but the escapee is a murderer,

441
00:28:47,230 --> 00:28:49,700
so the police contacted us for help
in publicizing his capture.

442
00:28:49,700 --> 00:28:52,740
He planned his escape
and injured himself beforehand.

443
00:28:52,970 --> 00:28:54,240
I'll get going.

444
00:29:00,309 --> 00:29:01,809
("A Prisoner Escapes
from National Forensic Hospital")

445
00:29:03,250 --> 00:29:04,809
(The police are looking for
Moon Sung Ho, who ran away...)

446
00:29:14,220 --> 00:29:15,259
Ha Jin?

447
00:29:15,490 --> 00:29:16,690
Surprise.

448
00:29:22,269 --> 00:29:23,900
- You.
- Are you surprised?

449
00:29:24,529 --> 00:29:27,269
Ms. Yeo is
more popular than I thought.

450
00:29:27,740 --> 00:29:31,369
I'm thinking of getting
her autograph now that I'm here.

451
00:29:31,369 --> 00:29:32,509
What do you think?

452
00:29:34,339 --> 00:29:37,109
To be honest,
Ms. Yeo and I met before.

453
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:39,650
You jerk.
You need to get out of there.

454
00:29:39,849 --> 00:29:41,549
Gosh, I knew you'd be like that.

455
00:29:42,650 --> 00:29:44,819
I'm the only one
who's concerned about Seo Yeon.

456
00:29:45,819 --> 00:29:49,630
Are you feeling desperate
to think of Yeo Ha Jin?

457
00:29:50,259 --> 00:29:52,759
Do your best to come
if you can be here.

458
00:29:53,230 --> 00:29:56,500
But back then and now,

459
00:29:57,700 --> 00:29:59,900
you'll never be able to stop me.

460
00:30:07,109 --> 00:30:08,109
Darn it.

461
00:30:42,180 --> 00:30:43,849
(Ha Jin)

462
00:30:50,250 --> 00:30:52,190
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

463
00:31:11,009 --> 00:31:12,509
What's your name?

464
00:31:15,980 --> 00:31:17,150
Don't you remember me?

465
00:31:24,190 --> 00:31:26,289
You really don't remember anything,
do you?

466
00:31:26,819 --> 00:31:30,130
That's really odd.
How can you forget that?

467
00:31:32,299 --> 00:31:33,529
Thanks for your help back then.

468
00:31:36,029 --> 00:31:37,099
Hello.

469
00:31:38,269 --> 00:31:40,470
I'm the guy who's dating Yeong.

470
00:31:45,140 --> 00:31:46,339
Seo Yeon and I...

471
00:31:49,710 --> 00:31:51,710
I'm the guy who's dating Yeong.

472
00:31:54,220 --> 00:31:55,390
I...

473
00:31:58,049 --> 00:31:59,859
love her a lot.

474
00:32:15,569 --> 00:32:16,640
Ha Na.

475
00:32:37,059 --> 00:32:39,400
(Find Me in Your Memory)

476
00:32:39,630 --> 00:32:41,059
What's with you?

477
00:32:41,059 --> 00:32:44,000
Why did you lie?
Why did you let me just forget her?

478
00:32:44,269 --> 00:32:46,000
I love you a lot, Ha Jin.

479
00:32:46,000 --> 00:32:48,569
Please let me be alone for a moment.

480
00:32:48,569 --> 00:32:51,809
It's about time you stopped.
It has been eight years already.

481
00:32:51,809 --> 00:32:53,480
I'm sorry I came too late.

482
00:32:53,480 --> 00:32:55,279
But nothing will change.

483
00:32:55,279 --> 00:32:56,410
Everything is in the past.

484
00:32:56,410 --> 00:32:58,720
Let's go back to the time
when we didn't know each other.

485
00:32:58,720 --> 00:33:00,849
- Are you with Ha Jin?
- Is something going on?

486
00:33:00,849 --> 00:33:03,119
She suddenly disappeared,
and she left her phone at home.

487
00:33:03,119 --> 00:33:05,759
You promised
you'll never say goodbye.

488
00:33:05,759 --> 00:33:08,490
I'm sorry.
I can't keep that promise.
